NEXT STEPS (PHASE 3 AND BEYOND)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Phase 3 is hardware. The key items I will be adding before any flight testing:

1. Update m in params.py to match the real all-up weight (~2 kg). This affects
   T_max, the hover thrust, and every sub-margin that involves thrust. Running
   hardware tests with m=1.0 will cause the margins to be miscalibrated.

2. Run the system identification experiment. Hover at d = 0.3m, 0.5m, 0.8m,
   1.2m. Log commanded thrust and IMU-measured acceleration at each position.
   Fit the residual acceleration to the c0, c1, c2 model. Update params.py.

3. Write the MAVLink interface. The Python simulation sends T and tau directly
   to the dynamics model. On hardware, the Jetson sends attitude setpoints to
   PX4 via MAVLink (pymavlink or MAVSDK). The translation layer between the
   CBF output and PX4 setpoint commands doesn't exist yet.

4. Build the LiDAR wall detection pipeline. The simulation assumes d is known
   perfectly. On hardware, d comes from fitting a plane to the Livox Mid-360
   point cloud in real time. This needs to run fast enough to feed the margin
   estimator at >50 Hz.

5. Tether first flights. Never untethered near the wall until hover at 0.5m
   is confirmed stable for 10+ minutes with M being logged from real sensors.

Phase 4 is validation: 30 docking trials vs the ETH Zurich ±10 cm scatter
benchmark and a portfolio write-up.

